       rmail - handle remote mail received via uucp

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       rrmmaaiill [--DD _d_o_m_a_i_n] [--TT] _u_s_e_r _._._.

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       RRmmaaiill   interprets  incoming  mail  received  via  uucp(1),  collapsing
       ``From'' lines in the form generated by  mail.local(8)  into  a  single
       line of the form ``return-path!sender'', and passing the processed mail
       on to sendmail(8).

       RRmmaaiill is explicitly designed for use with uucp and sendmail.

   FFllaaggss
       --DD     Use the specified  _d_o_m_a_i_n  instead  of  the  default  domain  of
              ``UUCP''.

       --TT     Turn on debugging.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       uucp(1), mail.local(8), sendmail(8)

HHIISSTTOORRYY
       The rrmmaaiill program appeared in 4.2BSD.

BBUUGGSS
       RRmmaaiill should not reside in /bin.



